_meanings:
A riddle, an
enigma, a conundrum. It is thus
defined in the {#vidagDamuKamaMqanaH#} - 
{#vyaktIkftya kamapyarTaM svarUpArTasya gopanAt . yatra#}
{#bAhyAMtarAvarTO kaTyete sA prahelikA#}. It is
{#ArTI#} or {#SAbdI; taruRyAliMgitaH kaMWe#} 
{#nitaMbasTalamASritaH . gurURAM sanniDAne'pi kaH#} 
{#kUjati muhurmuhuH#} (where the answer is  
{#IzadUnajalapUrRakuMBaH#}) is an instance of the
former kind; {#sadAri maDyApi na vEriyuktA#}
{#nitAMtaraktApyasitEva nityaM . yaToktavAdinyapi#}
{#nEva dUtI kA nAma kAMteti nivedayASu ..#}
(where the answer is {#sArikA#}), of the
latter. Daṇḍin, however, mentions
16 different kinds of {#pralehikA#}; see
<ls>Kāv. 3. 96-124</ls>.
